724851f-a.title: Manhattan: York Avenue - 61st Street
724851f-a.text:
York Avenue (name chsnged 1928 from Avenue A), east side, north from
and incluoing 6lst Street. On the N.E. corner of 62nd Street is
the pumping station of the Consolidated Gas Company, and behind
it may be seen the old American Malting Company plant, on 64th
Street east of the Avenue. It now belongs to George Ehret, and
will be demolished three years from the time of this picture.
Above 64th Street may be seen trees on the grounds of the Rockefeller
Institute for Medical Research.
September 15, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
